Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Composer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-7)

Refreshable elements can wrap content in the template that is often or sometimes updated, typically due to external data changes (such as date, pricing, etc.). A list of all the refreshables configured in the template can be found in the right side panel in the Composer. Clicking on a refreshable in the right side panel will indicate its location in the editor:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Refreshables panel*

If the content was modified in the document or if external data modification caused different content in the refreshable compared to the document, there will be a yellow rectangle indication:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Refreshables difference indication*

If there are too many refreshables in the document, users can check the 'Show different only' setting, which shows only refreshables with some differences:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Show different only filter*

This checkbox also triggers a refresh of the comparison data, as the comparison is currently not done on the fly, but only initially during document load and after changing the filter setting.

Similarly to insertion points, there is a preview functionality that allows users to check the most recent refreshable content:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*Refreshables preview*

Updating with new data is done by clicking on the update button:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Update refreshable*

By clicking on the 'Update All' button, all the refreshables in the document will be updated:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*Update all refreshables*

Updating a refreshable erases the previous content that was in the document. Typically, refreshable content should not be editable to prevent unintended data loss during the update operation. If a refreshable is configured to be editable, users need to be aware of the possible risk.

> Preview and undo functionality should help to prevent or recover from unintended document modifications.
